dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Kerasund-Karahissar, sheet 4. Series I.D.W.O. no. 1522
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. " Lith. at the Intell. Div. War Office, Jan. 1902." Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522. Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division. I.D.W.O. no. 1522. Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compiled at the Intelligence Division, War Office by Major F.R. Maunsell, R.A. from Admiralty Charts Nos. 2220, 2236, 2237, Major F.R. Maunsel Reconnaissances 1892, 1897, 1898, Various Sketches of Coast Districts supplied by H.B.M. Consulate, Trebizond." With a glossary. Set is complete, see index.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
